Description:
    Generates keys and certificates for root CA, intermediate CA and server

Example:
    bin/rails generate certificate --country XX --state Xxxx --location Xxxxx --organization xxxx --organization-unit xxxx --common-name xxxxx.xxx.xx

    This will create 7 files, where xxxxx.xxx.xx is the common-name defined in the command:
        storage/xxxxx.xxx.xx/root/cert.pem
        storage/xxxxx.xxx.xx/root/key.pem
        storage/xxxxx.xxx.xx/intermediate/cert.pem
        storage/xxxxx.xxx.xx/intermediate/key.pem
        storage/xxxxx.xxx.xx/server/cert.pem
        storage/xxxxx.xxx.xx/server/key.pem
        storage/xxxxx.xxx.xx/server/chain.pem
